{
  "id": "019d2436-ee45-71a0-8a96-a0d1bf9ab1ca",
  "content": "# Decision: Migrate Devcontainer Setup to Python + Taskfile\n\n## Decision\nReplace bash-based devcontainer setup orchestration (post-start.sh, post-create.sh) with:\n- **Taskfile** (go-task.github.io/task) for declarative task definitions with `status:` checks\n- **Python wrapper** (setup_wrapper.py) for `fcntl.flock` locking and boot-id state management\n- **Setup telemetry** (setup_telemetry.py) buffering step timing to JSON, ingesting into corvia via MCP\n\n## Why\nThe current bash lock/done-marker mechanism fails: mkdir locks survive SIGKILL, /tmp markers clear on restart, set -euo pipefail exits before done marker written. Fundamentally tracks \"have I run?\" instead of \"is it done?\"\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n1. **Pure Python (extend corvia-dev)** — chicken-and-egg problem (corvia-dev not installed during post-create), no declarative overview\n2. **Taskfile + bash wrapper** — bash is where fragility lives, flock fd tricks are error-prone\n3. **Just add flock to existing bash** — 80% fix but doesn't solve status detection or enable parallelism\n4. **Rust binary** — slowest iteration cycle for setup scripts\n\n## Key Design Choices\n- Double-checked locking pattern in Python wrapper (check before AND after flock)\n- `except OSError` not bare `except` for boot_id (prevents silent \"unknown\" match)\n- `subprocess.run` not `execvp` for bash fallback (so done marker still written)\n- Auth task intentionally has NO status check (credentials may refresh)\n- GPU-absent status checks return \"skip\" not \"fail\"\n- Telemetry uses atomic JSON writes (tmp+rename), idempotent ingestion\n- State lives in `.devcontainer/.task/` not `/tmp`\n\n## Reviewed by\nTri-persona review (Senior SWE, QA, PM) — 1 critical bug fixed (double-checked locking), 10 warns addressed, 18-point verification plan.",
